      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Simple Chatbot\n\nThis is a very basic chatbot using either a local model or OpenAI model.\n\nIt is connected to the Ollama local model first. \n\nTo connect it to OpenAI model, delete the link between `AI Agent`'s `Chat Model` and link the `OpenChatModel`\n\n### Step to rebuild this workflow: (local model)\n- Start with a node:  **`When chat message received`**\n    - define the chatbot conversation page\n    - set the parameters (initial message, options like Title and Subtitle\n- Add a node: **`AI Agent`**\n    - Define what input field is used as user prompt\n    - Define a system prompt\n- Add a local model:\n    - click on + below `Chat Model`\n    - select `Ollama Chat Model`\n    - select or create a `credential` for Ollama (`http://ollama:11434`)\n    - select one of the models available\n        - if model not available, add in the file `list-of-models.txt` and then run the script to download the model (MacOS: `scripts/download-models.sh` or Windows: `scripts/download-models.bat`)\n- Add a memory to the bot\n    - click on + below `Memory`\n    - select `Simple Memory`\n\n",
        "height": 656,
        "width": 608,
        "color": 7
      },
